OL,3,CCall for renters in Wales to get
OL,4,Ccompensation for no-fault eviction
OL,6,FWith help from the council, Jeffrey
OL,7,Fsaid he was eventually able to find
OL,8,Fsomewhere to rent. Jeffrey says
OL,9,Fcompensation for tenants "would go a
OL,10,Flong way to help," but that it would
OL,11,Fneed to be "tightly controlled." He
OL,12,Fadded that he feels tenants of no-
OL,13,Ffault evictions should not have to pay
OL,14,Flegal costs.
OL,16,FThe Welsh Government told the
OL,17,FCommittee that the existing six-month
OL,18,Fwarning that a landlord must give a
OL,19,Ftenant means that Wales currently has
OL,20,Fthe toughest protections for tenants
OL,21,Fin the UK.
